President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring March 26, 2010, as "Education and Sharing Day, U.S.A." In the proclamation, Obama emphasizes the importance of instilling a love for learning and compassion in children. He states that for America to thrive in the 21st century, it is crucial to have a well-educated workforce that can compete in the global economy. Additionally, he highlights the need for citizens who are not only educated but also driven by their humanity and civic virtue. The proclamation also pays tribute to Rabbi Menachem Mendel Schneerson, who promoted the values of education and kindness. Obama calls upon all Americans to observe this day with appropriate ceremonies and activities.